# Calendar & Meeting Reminders

## Product truth

- **No union-wide calendar module** ‚Äî no `/app/calendar`, `/events`, or `/meetings` hub route (until Phase A/R1 ships a real page)
- **No automated email, push, SMS, or cron reminders** ‚Äî no SMTP provider, no `/api/notifications`, no scheduled jobs
- **`/app/overdue`** tracks **grievance CA step deadlines only** ‚Äî not membership meetings or scheduled grievance meetings
- **No `/member` portal** ‚Äî live RSVP (when built) is a **public token form** `/r/[token]`, not member self-service

Full spec: [`docs/modules/CALENDAR_MEETINGS.md`](../../docs/modules/CALENDAR_MEETINGS.md)

## Two surfaces (do not conflate)

| Surface | Auth | Meeting scope | Persistence |
|---------|------|---------------|-------------|
| **Officer Hub** | Login + MFA + grievance RBAC | Grievance `ScheduledMeeting` per case | Memory adapter (`src/types/qol.ts`) |
| **Public Comms** | None (client-only) | Announcement + offline RSVP exports | None ‚Äî export PNG/PDF/doc/xlsx/ics only |

**Terminology guard:** "Meeting scheduler" in the codebase = **grievance meetings**, not monthly membership / local executive meetings.

## Shipped today

### Officer Hub (grievance-scoped)
- Meeting scheduler + ICS: `GrievanceDetail`, `POST /api/grievances/[id]/meetings`
- Deadline ICS: 1-hour block around CA step `dueAt` on grievance detail
- Email drafts (copy-only): `step1_meeting`, `extension_request`, `member_update` via `/api/grievances/[id]/email-draft`
- Overdue board: `/app/overdue` ‚Äî grievance deadlines from `deadlines.ts`

### Public Comms (announcement + offline RSVP)
- Board Notice (`/tools/board-notice`) ‚Äî `noticeType: "meeting"`; PNG/PDF export
- Document Generator `quick-event` ‚Äî hybrid **LEC RSVP Excel**: Attending + **On site/Remote**, quorum board, **food heads** (on-site only), dietary; **`.ics`** from calendar start/end; **copy-only RSVP invite email** (`src/lib/comms/event-email.ts`); PPTX
- Event ICS helper: `src/lib/calendar/event-ics.ts`
- Graphic Maker `meetingNotice` starter; Meeting Backgrounds (Zoom/Teams branding)
- Website Template ‚Äî static ZIP with `mailto:`; no embedded calendar widget

### Sample email placement (decided)
- **Event RSVP invite email = public Comms** (Document Generator) ‚Äî announcement class, no PII, copy-only / `mailto:`
- **Grievance email drafts = Hub** (`/api/grievances/[id]/email-draft`) ‚Äî confidential, MFA + audit
- Do not move the event invite into the Hub or reuse the grievance draft API for it

### ICS utility (`src/lib/calendar/ics.ts`)
- `buildIcsEvent()`, `downloadIcs()` ‚Äî export-only, generated on demand
- **Limitations:** UTC only; no `VTIMEZONE`, `RRULE`, `VALARM`, or `ATTENDEE`; placeholder organizer `noreply@local-union-hub.local`
- Extend here if recurrence or calendar-native alarms ship ‚Äî do not duplicate elsewhere

## RSVP phases (see full spec)

| Phase | What | When |
|-------|------|------|
| **R0** | Offline hybrid LEC RSVP (quorum + on-site food) + `.ics` + copy-only invite email | Shipped |
| **R1** | `UnionMeeting` + `joinMode` RSVP + Hub tallies + `/r/[token]` | After Postgres + RLS |
| **R2** | Officer banner + copy-only reminder with RSVP link | After R1 |
| **R3** | Transactional officer (and optional confirm) email | ARCHITECTURE v2+ |

## Auth matrix

| Action | Requires |
|--------|----------|
| Public Comms meeting tools / offline RSVP export | None |
| List grievance meetings / download ICS / email drafts | Session + MFA + `assertGrievanceView` |
| Schedule grievance meeting / log comms | Session + MFA + `assertGrievanceEdit` |
| Steward mobile read-only | Hides schedule form; **still allows** ICS download + email drafts |
| Future public token RSVP POST | Valid token only ‚Äî no session; rate-limit |

## Realistic near-term (if stakeholder approves)

1. **`LocalMeetingSchedule` in tenant config** ‚Äî recurring membership meeting (title, RRULE, location, public vs internal description)
2. **Public "next meeting" snippet** ‚Äî date/time/location only; no member lists or strategy
3. **Extend `ics.ts`** ‚Äî `RRULE:FREQ=MONTHLY`, optional `VALARM`
4. **Hub in-app banner** + copy-only `membership_meeting_reminder` draft template
5. **Phase R1 RSVP** ‚Äî separate `UnionMeeting` / token form (not grievance `ScheduledMeeting`)

## Explicitly deferred (do not build without milestone)

- Union calendar grid / month view
- Member email lists or subscription management
- Auto-send email (blocked on ARCHITECTURE v2+ transactional email)
- Cron / workers / `vercel.json` scheduled functions
- Browser push / web notifications
- `/member` portal (token RSVP ‚âÝ portal)
- ICS import or public subscribe feed (Phase D ‚Äî after Postgres + compliance review)
- Memory-only `UnionMeeting` store before Postgres

**Dependencies:** Postgres + RLS (roadmap #1) before persisting schedules/RSVPs; transactional email before auto-send; TOTP MFA (roadmap #7) before expanding notification surfaces.

## Agent alignment principles

1. **Meet need with existing tools first** ‚Äî Board Notice + Document Generator RSVP pack + personal/event `.ics` is the supported workflow today
2. **No auto-send without v2 email** ‚Äî copy-only drafts are intentional (`grievance-module.mdc`)
3. **Grievance ‚âÝ membership** ‚Äî do not reuse `ScheduledMeeting` for local monthly meetings or RSVPs; use `LocalMeetingSchedule` / `UnionMeeting` scoped by `unionId` + `localId`
4. **Public = less detail** ‚Äî non-logged-in surfaces show date/time/location (+ RSVP response fields only)
5. **Postgres before persistence** ‚Äî no new memory-only meeting/RSVP store; tenant seed JSON for static config only until DB lands
6. **Roadmap order** ‚Äî Postgres ‚Üí onboarding ‚Üí attachments ‚Üí then meeting config / live RSVP

## Do Not

- Auto-send email drafts or member communications
- Conflate grievance meetings with membership/monthly local meetings in UI copy or data models
- Add nav stubs for calendar/meetings without a shipped page
- Build marketing broadcast or member email collection without PIPEDA review (`docs/COMPLIANCE.md`)
- Treat Comms meeting tools as live scheduling or reminder systems ‚Äî they are announcement / offline-tracking exports
- Add SMTP, cron, or push as a side quest when asked for "monthly meeting reminders" ‚Äî document gaps and phased plan first
- Build a first-party `/member` portal for RSVP ‚Äî use public token form instead
